This paper deals with the joint transmission of information and energy in wireless systems, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of information theory (cs.IT) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the modeling of stochastic energy utilization requirements and the imposition of constraints on battery underflow and overflow, which are topics that fall under the category of control and systems engineering (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper mentions body area networks with implantable devices, which is a topic that falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper discusses the use of codes to achieve the joint transmission of information and energy, which is a topic that falls under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR).
